id: pm-4oww
title: Extension activation adds ~200ms to every command when bundled packages are installed
description: "Measured 2026-07-04 (best-of-3, warm, node dist/cli.js): bare workspace list/get/create = 195-232ms; same commands with all 11 bundled packages installed = 361-461ms (health 569ms). pm --version = 52ms, so ~150ms is ESM import of the CLI itself and installed extensions roughly double per-command latency. Candidates: lazy per-command activation via activation.commands narrowing for built-ins that register global surfaces, module-graph precompute/cache for extension entries, or a persisted activation manifest so unaffected commands skip loading entries entirely."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[2]: extensions,performance
created_at: "2026-07-04T06:29:59.294Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-04T14:38:43.931Z"
assignee: claude-code-agent
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: Warm per-command latency with all bundled packages installed within 1.5x of bare workspace (measured via best-of-3 node dist/cli.js timings).
parent: pm-ugqx
comments[12]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T11:15:27.399Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: implemented command-scoped import filtering. loadExtensions now preserves full discovery but imports only extensions accepted by the CLI activation probe; CLI snapshot cache is scoped by activation probe; manifests with explicit activation.commands no longer load solely because they also declare hooks. Focused checks passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-loader.spec.ts (107 tests), node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts (119 tests), pnpm typecheck. Temp workspace with explicit install '*' installed 11 packages and improved profile list loaded extensions to 3 (governance-audit no longer always activates); shell best-of-7 still did not consistently meet the <=1.5x target (bare/list 174ms vs package/list 323ms after local lifecycle simulation), so item remains open for the next cheap-activation/persisted-manifest lever."
  "2026-07-04T11:42:53.432Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence update: command-scoped activation filtering now preserves full discovery while filtering imports by activation probe, scopes runtime snapshot cache by normalized activation scope, avoids double activation for dynamic/template/search commands, and keeps hook/render-only extensions globally active without re-broadening command-bearing explicit activation manifests. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/extension-startup.integration.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-loader.spec.ts; pnpm typecheck; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5337 tests, 100/100/100/100); pnpm lint; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate; pnpm security:scan; pnpm quality:docs-skills; node scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.mjs --check; pnpm changelog:pm:check; pm health --check-only --summary --json. Item remains open because the package-vs-bare latency acceptance target still needs another lever."
  "2026-07-04T12:04:46.172Z",claude-code-agent,"Review-response evidence: addressed Gemini inline findings by accepting function/class-shaped extension module/default exports through shared asPropertyRecord runtime narrowing (loader + SDK harness parity), and by extracting Commander\\'s exact offending pm context argument before argv fallback. Focused verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts (117 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/error-guidance.spec.ts (30 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-loader.spec.ts (107 tests). Broad verification passed: pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint; git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5338 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines: 32890/32890, 23394/23394, 6469/6469, 31600/31600)."
  "2026-07-04T12:40:03.203Z",unknown,"Review-response evidence: addressed Cubic/Gemini follow-ups by adding multi-extension activation/capability summary filters for package describe unions, scoping type-stripping runtime-loader fallback to the attempted runtime path, preserving list sort constant exports, and making ctx/context fallback parsing alias/flag aware. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/core/extensions/activation-summary.spec.ts tests/unit/extensions/extension-describe.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.spec.ts; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/cli/error-guidance.spec.ts tests/unit/extensions/extension-describe.spec.ts tests/unit/core/extensions/activation-summary.spec.ts; pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint; git diff --check; full node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5353 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines: 32922/32922, 23423/23423, 6470/6470, 31632/31632); node scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.mjs --check; pnpm changelog:pm && pnpm changelog:pm:check; pnpm audit --audit-level moderate; pnpm security:scan; pm health --check-only --summary --json. pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift has clean history drift and the pre-existing closed-item resolution metadata warning validate_resolution_missing_fields:267."
  "2026-07-04T12:40:12.173Z",claude-code-agent,"Author correction: the immediately preceding review-response evidence comment was added by claude-code-agent; PM_AUTHOR was missing from that shell invocation. Continuing this item with PM_AUTHOR=claude-code-agent for subsequent mutations."
  "2026-07-04T13:10:13.439Z",claude-code-agent,"Review-response evidence update: addressed the current-head bot findings after 58eabe15 by preserving global hook/parser/preflight/renderer activation for mixed hook+command extensions, skipping --pm-path/--path values in pm context fallback guidance, and reading manifest metadata from callable SDK test modules/default exports. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/error-guidance.spec.ts tests/unit/cli/cli-main-errors.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts (270 tests); pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint; git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5354 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines: 32923/32923, 23410/23410, 6470/6470, 31633/31633); pnpm changelog:pm && pnpm changelog:pm:check (CHANGELOG unchanged, pm-changelog 2026.6.30); pnpm security:scan; npm audit retry via NPM_CONFIG_FETCH_RETRIES=1 NPM_CONFIG_FETCH_TIMEOUT=120000 pnpm audit --audit-level moderate (no known vulnerabilities); pm telemetry flush succeeded at 2026-07-04T13:09:31.997Z; pm health --check-only --summary --json is clean; pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift has clean history drift and the existing closed-item resolution metadata warning validate_resolution_missing_fields:267."
  "2026-07-04T13:21:31.042Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: addressed current-head Gemini context guidance feedback by preserving dotted offending arguments from Commander messages and accepting raw ctx command names in the context guidance guard. Focused validation passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/error-guidance.spec.ts (36 tests), pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint, git diff --check."
  "2026-07-04T13:32:18.115Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence update: reran full coverage after context guidance branch coverage fix. Validation passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/error-guidance.spec.ts (36 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (263 files, 5356 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines: 32923/32923, 23412/23412, 6470/6470, 31633/31633). Earlier same-head checks also passed: pnpm typecheck, pnpm lint, git diff --check."
  "2026-07-04T13:48:55.856Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: addressed remaining PR review feedback on context argument guidance and SDK harness callable-module manifest inference. Context fallback now skips all context value-taking flags before suggesting pm get, and createExtensionTestHarness no longer treats a callable module's built-in function name as manifest metadata unless explicit manifest/default metadata is present. Verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/cli/error-guidance.spec.ts tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts passed 154 tests; pnpm typecheck passed; pnpm lint passed (ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, static quality gate); git diff --check passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 263 files / 5357 tests with 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines."
  "2026-07-04T14:03:46.277Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: addressed current-head Gemini follow-up on SDK harness default callable exports. readTestExtensionManifest now ignores bare function/class default exports for direct manifest fallback while preserving explicit default.manifest metadata, preventing built-in function/class names from becoming extension names. Added createExtensionTestHarness regression for a bare default callable with no manifest/options name. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts (117 tests); pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint (ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, static quality gate); git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 263 files / 5357 tests with 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines (32923/32923, 23414/23414, 6470/6470, 31633/31633)."
  "2026-07-04T14:21:19.384Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: addressed current-head Gemini follow-ups on package runtime loader path normalization and package describe not-found hints. The generated first-party runtime loaders now avoid regex escape ambiguity by using split/join normalization for Windows backslashes, and package vocabulary describe errors list source package names when available instead of only internal extension names. Verification passed: node scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.mjs --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/extensions/extension-describe.spec.ts tests/unit/scripts/gen-package-runtime-loaders.spec.ts tests/unit/packages/runtime-loaders.spec.ts (55 tests); pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint (ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, static quality gate); git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 263 files / 5358 tests with 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines (32926/32926, 23419/23419, 6470/6470, 31638/31638)."
  "2026-07-04T14:38:43.931Z",claude-code-agent,"Evidence: addressed current-head CodeRabbit duplicate-shape feedback by moving extension activate export detection into shared resolveActivatablePropertyRecord and using it from both runtime loading and the SDK test harness. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/sdk/sdk-index.spec.ts tests/unit/extensions/extension-loader.spec.ts tests/unit/core/shared/shared-primitives.spec.ts (249 tests); pnpm typecheck; pnpm lint (ESLint, jscpd 0 clones, static quality gate); git diff --check; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed 263 files / 5358 tests with 100% statements, 100% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines (32924/32924, 23417/23417, 6471/6471, 31636/31636)."
notes[5]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T06:44:04.727Z",maintainer-agent,"Raw timing evidence (sandbox1, best-of-3): list 361ms, get 373ms, next 410ms, search 446ms, create 461ms, update 422ms, health 569ms, context 399ms vs bare workspace list 195ms, list-all 199ms, create 232ms; pm --version 52ms."
  "2026-07-04T07:05:01.517Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-04 optimization landed (uncommitted): SDK entrypoints (sdk/index, runtime, testing) now bundle in the SAME esbuild invocation as the CLI with shared chunks; package.json exports point import/default at dist/cli-bundle/sdk*.js (types stay on dist/sdk/*.d.ts). Extensions importing @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk now reuse chunk modules the CLI already loaded — one shared copy of core state instead of two. Cold dist/sdk/index.js import was 226ms (138 local modules); bundled sdk.js import 79ms; shared-chunk variant near-free after CLI load. Warm best-of-N pm list with 11 packages: 651ms -> 331-385ms (bare 189-263ms). Remaining ~150ms = per-extension ESM resolution through 11 node_modules symlinks + 11 entry.ts type-strip imports + activation; next lever is activation.commands narrowing / persisted activation manifest."
  "2026-07-04T07:22:59.411Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-04 full coverage gate green after change: 5338 tests, 100% statements/branches/functions/lines. Spec updates: release-readiness-runtime + package-manifest exports assertions moved to dist/cli-bundle/sdk*.js paths."
  "2026-07-04T08:15:10.095Z",maintainer-agent,"Activation-narrowing audit: extensionNeedsActivationForProbe already skips extensions whose declared activation.commands don't match. Always-activated today: pm-governance-audit (hooks), pm-lifecycle-hooks (hooks), pm-command-kit (parser) — genuinely global; pm-kanban declares only [schema] with NO activation.commands so it falls into the conservative tier and activates on EVERY command. Remaining lever is making activation itself cheap (per-package prebundled entry chunks or persisted activation manifest), not more narrowing."
  "2026-07-04T10:37:20.716Z",maintainer-agent,"2026-07-04 contention-free re-measurement from fresh 2026.7.4 tarball pack in CJS sandbox (best-of-5, warm): list 395ms / get 418ms / next 518ms with all 11 packages vs bare list 192ms; pm --version 63ms. Ratio ~2.06x — improved from pre-fix 651ms but acceptance (≤1.5x bare) not yet met. Item stays open; remaining lever per activation-narrowing audit is cheap activation (prebundled per-package entry chunks or persisted activation manifest) plus giving pm-kanban explicit activation.commands so it leaves the conservative always-activate tier."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-04T07:05:04.581Z",maintainer-agent,"Extension SDK imports resolved through the package exports to the unbundled dist/sdk graph while the CLI ran from its bundle — two copies of core, ~226ms extra ESM cost. Bundling SDK entrypoints in the same esbuild call as the CLI (entryPoints object: main/sdk/sdk-runtime/sdk-testing, splitting on) makes extensions share the CLI's already-loaded chunks. CPU profiles show source-mapped original filenames, so dist/sdk/*.js frames can appear even when only the bundle loads."
